	DRINK is the bartender book!<figcaption>
</figure>

One of the servers roaming
the bar instantly recognizes Brage and sets us up at a nice table right by the
courtyard.

"For you, my friends, I would recommend the 'Bun' to get the full Norwegian
experience. It's made with _______________ and topped with a vanilla pastry.
I would recommend drinking half the cocktail, eating the bun, then noticing how
it affects the flavor of the drink."

"I don't know about you guys but I'm sold"

"A round of Buns for the fellas"

The drink is meant to represent skolebr&oslash;d, a traditional Norwegian sweet
roll filled with custard & topped with icing. The tasty treat was typically
packed as a dessert in the lunchboxes of schoolchildren, hence the translation
of the Norwegian "school bread".

